### Description

My app has hash enabled for routing. When writing e2e tests with protractor, I try to navigate to the sign up page by passing the relative path and expecting it to be appended to the baseUrl. Something like this in my Page Object: 

`return browser.get('/authentication/sign-up');`

Apparently it tries to navigate to `http://localhost:4200/authentication/sign-up` instead of  `http://localhost:4200/#/authentication/sign-up`. I've tried changing the baseUrl in the protractor.conf.js to `http://localhost:4200/#` but that didn't help. I've even logged `browser.baseUrl` and it's value is always `http://localhost:4200` no matter what value I define in protractor.conf.js
